      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, this is much better. they can definitely use that social contract angle. \n\nto really round this out, i want them to be ready for the inevitable \"humanitarian\" pushback. some of the more hardcore arguments they'll face involve the moral obligation to help migrants or the idea that borders are inherently unjust. \n\nto prep for that, can you give me a breakdown of how a debater would professionally counter those humanitarian arguments using the points you just mentioned? like, how do they frame the priority of national stability over individual migration rights without sounding heartless or making it a purely emotional debate?",
