      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sophisticated counter reframes the debate from individual morality to systemic responsibility. Your students should argue that a functional, stable society is the prerequisite for *any* morality, meaning a government’s primary duty is to its established citizenry and national security. They can assert that while compassion is valuable, it cannot supersede the fundamental legal obligation to maintain the rule of law for all residents. By framing their position as prioritizing the collective security and stability of the nation, they elevate the argument beyond simple callousness.",
      "source": "target",
